modules.description: Provides functions to execute and evaluate OCaml code within a Js_of_ocaml toplevel environment. It handles string-based command execution, controls output formatting, and supports code highlighting during evaluation. Used to dynamically run OCaml snippets and inspect results in a JavaScript-compatible runtime.

Converts OCaml bytecode into executable JavaScript, enabling deployment of OCaml code in web browsers and Node.js environments. Supports direct integration with browser APIs through generated bindings. Facilitates execution of OCaml programs without modifying existing OCaml libraries or toolchains.

Executes and evaluates OCaml code in a Js_of_ocaml toplevel, processing string commands and managing output formatting and code highlighting. It supports dynamic execution of OCaml snippets and provides access to evaluation results. Key data types include strings for commands and results, with operations for execution and formatting. Users can run arbitrary OCaml code, capture outputs, and display formatted results in a web environment.
